Ad Text:
About the role

Join DataIQ as we expand our Data & AI practice to build modern data products on Microsoft Fabric. You'll be part of the team that owns ingestion, orchestration and transformation Microsoft Fabric, Spark and Power BI, delivering a variety of services to our clients that power enterprise semantic models and reports.

Australian work rights are required for this position.

What you'll do

Build and manage the Microsoft Fabric platform for client engagements, including governance, capacity planning, and performance optimisation.

Build and Oversee the Reporting function, ensuring timely delivery of semantic models and Power BI reports aligned with business needs.

Ingest and transform data using Fabric Data Factory, pipelines, and Spark notebooks (PySpark).

Model curated Delta tables and medallion layers optimized for Direct Lake and semantic models.

Automate reliability: parameterized pipelines, scheduling, monitoring, alerting; build runbooks for recovery.

Tune performance and cost (partitioning strategies, incremental refresh, capacity awareness).

Collaborate with stakeholders to align data products with strategic goals and reporting requirements.

What you'll bring

Hands-on experience with Microsoft Fabric (Data Factory, Synapse Data Engineering) and Spark/PySpark, with a minimum of 3 years' experience with Data Factory.

A minimum of 1 years hands-on Microsoft Fabric experience is required.

Strong SQL and Delta Lake experience; medallion architecture patterns.

Deep knowledge of OneLake, Data Factory in Fabric, Synapse Data Engineering/Spark, Real-Time Analytics, and Power BI (Service, Desktop).

Experience managing enterprise reporting functions and aligning data models with business KPIs.

CI/CD and deployment pipelines knowledge; Git familiarity.

Nice to have: KQL, streaming/Eventstreams, Databricks/Azure background, Purview lineage.

Certification preferred: Fabric Data Engineer Associate and PL-300 familiarity.

How to apply

Apply with your CV and a short cover letter highlighting recent Fabric/Spark projects. Portfolio or Git links welcome.

Our mission is to make fresh fruits and vegetables a more loved and essential part of everyone's life.

Perfection Fresh is one of Australia‚Äôs largest privately owned fresh produce companies that‚Äôs been on an exciting journey of innovation and growth since 1978.
We‚Äôre an Australian-based business that grows, packs, and markets fresh produce both domestically and internationally. You‚Äôll recognize our produce ‚Äì Qukes¬Æ, Broccolini¬Æ, Calypso¬Æ mangoes, and more.

Our history 45-year history is one of continuous progress. We‚Äôre the market leader in our field and we‚Äôve been listed on the Australian Financial Review‚Äôs top 100 private companies in Australia.
We employ more than 2,000 people across a portfolio of farming sites, high-tech production facilities, research, corporate offices, and national logistics operations.

Learn more about us and discover other exciting opportunities at www.perfection.com.au.

Drive the future of data at Perfection Fresh!


We‚Äôre looking for an experienced Enterprise Data Platform Lead to design, build, and manage our cutting-edge data platform powered by Microsoft Fabric. This is a pivotal role in delivering our Data Strategy, enabling secure, high-quality, and scalable data solutions that power reporting, analytics, AI/ML, and operational excellence across the organisation.

What you‚Äôll do
Lead the development and management of the enterprise data platform built on Microsoft Fabric.
Design and implement robust, scalable data pipelines and models to support diverse business needs.
Champion best practices in data engineering, governance, and security.
Drive innovation in data architecture and enable enterprise-wide decision-making through trusted, high-performance data solutions.

¬†




Desired Skills and Experience

Data Engineering Leadership
Minimum 5 years‚Äô experience in data engineering with proven leadership in Microsoft data technologies.

Microsoft Fabric Expertise
Hands-on experience delivering enterprise-scale solutions using Microsoft Fabric components, including OneLake, Lakehouse, Pipelines, and Real-Time Analytics.

Advanced Analytics & BI
Strong proficiency in Power BI, Azure Synapse, Data Factory, and Dataverse to enable scalable reporting and predictive modelling.

Technical Skills
Proficient in T-SQL, Python, and Spark within the Microsoft ecosystem, with deep knowledge of data modelling, lakehouse/warehouse architecture, and ETL/ELT best practices.

Data Integration & Transformation
Experience managing ingestion and transformation of diverse data sources such as APIs, databases, files, IoT, and cloud systems.

Governance & Compliance
Solid understanding of data governance, security, and metadata management, ideally leveraging Microsoft Purview for lineage and classification.

Leadership & Collaboration
Demonstrated ability to lead technical teams, mentor engineers, and deliver in agile environments while partnering effectively with business stakeholders.

Communication Skills
Excellent ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear business outcomes and engage stakeholders at all levels.

Our Australia-based AI-first Ed-Tech is solving this!

Mission-driven Ed-Tech sector leader

LLM / NLP / AI production systems

Sydney Head office / hybrid / remote

Decades-long university partnerships / established market player

An exciting opportunity now exists to join one of the fastest growing and most innovative companies in the dynamic education technology sector - Studiosity.

Now reaching over 1.8 million students across the UK, USA, Canada, Australia, NZ, UAE and beyond ‚Äì Studiosity is the premium partner of choice amongst educational institutions.

This makes us uniquely positioned to win and keep growing our mission to be able to enable better learning experiences and equal opportunity for students.




What you will do

Reporting to the Head of AI, you will join our Product Platform team as an experienced AI Engineer, leading the experimentation, design and development of market-leading generative AI education solutions. Your work will directly support our mission to improve life chances for students everywhere.

This role places you at the forefront of defining how the next generation learns - inventing new ways for students to interact with knowledge, practice skills, and receive personalised feedback.

A critical part of your work will be evolving our AI guardrails and quality systems, ensuring that all AI-generated feedback is safe, ethical, pedagogically sound, and supporting learning outcomes. Our AI team works closely with our Academic Standards team to ensure we focus on the high educational standards. You‚Äôll help shape not only the product experience, but also the principles and practices that underpin responsible AI in education.




About you

You are an experienced AI Engineer with strong foundations in machine learning, software engineering, and modern generative AI techniques.¬†

You will ideally have:

3+ years of experience designing, building, and operating scalable AI pipelines across data collection, evaluation, deployment, and monitoring.

2+ years of commercial experience working on NLP, large language models, or document understanding/analysis applications.

Strong understanding of machine learning fundamentals, model evaluation, data preprocessing, and robust software engineering practices.

Experience developing intelligent search systems and/or anomaly detection algorithms is a plus.¬†

Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, GCP, or Azure) and associated AI/ML services.

A demonstrated ability and enthusiasm for mentoring and guiding engineers, fostering growth and technical excellence across the team.

Demonstrated active use of modern AI tools in the development process is expected.¬†

Experienced with Python.




Why Studiosity?

Studiosity is an amazing place to work: In addition to our noble purpose of increasing life chances for students, we benefit from a low ego, non-corporate and lifestyle-friendly work ethic and culture. These are complemented by an exceptional passion and drive for lifelong learning in which everyone stays results-driven and proud of the work we deliver every day.


To express your interest please forward a cover letter accompanied by your current resume. Thanks for your consideration and we look forward to hearing from you.

Better and fairer care. Always.

St Vincent's has been a leader in Australia's health and aged care landscape for more than 165 years. Since our founders, the Sisters of Charity, opened our first hospital in 1857, our services and nearly 30,000 people have been behind some of Australia's most important medical breakthroughs. We are a microcosm of Australia's health and aged care system and are uniquely positioned to lead and respond to our rapidly changing environment.

We are looking for a special kind of person - a St Vincent's kind of person. Someone who puts excellence, compassion, connection and caring for other people at the heart of everything they do.

Are you a hands-on, strategic Senior AI Architect & Developer ready to lead the future of Artificial Intelligence in a mission-driven healthcare environment? Join St Vincent's Health Australia (SVHA), a non-profit health organisation renowned for exceptional, compassionate care and industry-leading research.

You will be the lead technical authority for AI, translating ambitious ideas into tangible, governed, and impactful tools that enable remote patient monitoring, predictive care models, and intelligent clinical decision support-bringing hospital-grade care safely into patients' homes while reducing administrative burden on our 30,000 staff.

This is a foundational leadership role with significant growth potential. As SVHA's AI delivery capabilities mature over the next 3 years, this role will evolve from hands-on technical architect to strategic AI leader.

Role Impact: Accelerating AI Adoption Safely

This role is the core technical engine of SVHA's AI ambitions across Generative AI, Machine Learning, Computer Vision, and predictive analytics. You will act as the critical bridge between frontline clinical/operational challenges and enterprise-grade, production-ready solutions that enable our radical shift from hospital-centric to home-centric care delivery.

Your impact will be the safe, rapid acceleration of our AI adoption journey-directly enabling the transformation of healthcare delivery models that will define the future of Australian healthcare.

This is not just about building AI models; it's about fundamentally reimagining how care is delivered, monitored, and optimized when the hospital walls disappear and the patient's home becomes the primary care setting. You will architect the AI capabilities that make virtual wards safe, predictive deterioration detection possible, and remote care coordination seamless across our federated ministry spanning public hospitals, private hospitals, aged care, and virtual health services.

The right candidate will grow alongside our AI maturity journey, shaping not just the technical architecture but the entire operating model, team structure, and strategic direction. This is a rare opportunity to build something from the ground up within a nationally significant healthcare organization, with the autonomy, resources, and executive support to make it succeed.

Key Accountabilities: Managing Today

As the Senior AI Architect & Developer, you will be responsible for:

Strategic Vision: Own the multi-year AI technical roadmap, ensuring alignment with the EMR strategy, data platform capabilities, and the organisation's 2030 vision.
AI Architecture & Blueprint: Design and own the enterprise AI technical architecture, solutions, and technology standards that will serve as the secure foundation for all future AI development.
Hands-on Development: Lead the hands-on development, validation, and deployment lifecycle to translate complex clinical and operational problems into robust, production-ready AI solutions.
Vendor & Technology Assessment: Lead the technical evaluation and security assessment of all third-party AI vendor solutions, ensuring they are secure and fit-for-purpose.
Model Lifecycle Management: Implement and manage the full lifecycle of all production AI models, including continuous monitoring, performance tuning, and model retraining.
AI Acceleration: Develop and curate a library of reusable "AI Accelerators" (e.g., standard code libraries, solution patterns) to dramatically reduce the time-to-value for future projects.
Governance & Safety: Embed AI safety, ethics, and governance (from the AI Framework) into the technical design of every solution, ensuring all models are robust, explainable, and compliant with healthcare regulations and data privacy standards.

What You'll Bring

We are seeking a senior, hands-on technologist who is both an architect and a developer-a pragmatic problem-solver with deep, enterprise-level expertise in building and scaling secure AI/ML solutions.

Essential Experience and Skills

Experience: Demonstrated experience (10+ years) in data science, software engineering, or a related field, with at least 3+ years in a senior or architect-level role.
Hands-on experience building and deploying solutions using Generative AI and Large Language Models (LLMs).
AI/ML Expertise: Proven, hands-on experience in designing, building, and deploying enterprise-scale AI/ML models (e.g., NLP, computer vision, predictive analytics) from pilot to production.
MLOps Mastery: Deep experience in designing MLOps and DataOps pipelines for model training, versioning, deployment, and continuous monitoring.
Cloud & Programming: Extensive experience with a major cloud platform, preferably Microsoft Azure (e.g., Azure ML, Azure OpenAI Service, Azure Data Factory), and Expert-level programming skills (e.g., Python).
Architecture: Deep understanding of software architecture principles, API design, microservices, and containerisation (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes).
Mindset: A "safety-first" and ethical mindset with a strong understanding of data privacy, security, and the principles of responsible AI.

Minimum Education Requirements

A post-graduate degree (Master's or PhD) in Computer Science, AI, Data Science, or a related quantitative field.

Desirable

Experience working in the healthcare sector or another highly regulated industry.

If you are driven to achieve results , possess strong technical and analytical skills , and want to contribute to a workplace that is safe and promotes personal wellbeing, we encourage you to apply.

Things that work for you:

Ability to visibly see your impact on the business and its service
Competitive salary packaging options
Discounted private health insurance
Employee Assistance Program for staff and their families
Access to the Fitness Passport (FP)

At St Vincent's we value inclusivity and diversity and acknowledge the importance of creating a work environment that is welcoming, safe, fair and impartial and invites people from all backgrounds to join us.

Pre-Employment Checks

Your employment is conditional upon the completion of all required pre-employment checks, including relevant immunisations.

Equal Opportunity

We celebrate diversity & inclusion and are committed to equal employment opportunity for everyone.

How To Apply

Please submit your application via the Apply button, include your resume and a brief cover letter outlining your experience and suitability.

Respectfully, no recruitment agencies.

Senior Data Engineer / Snowflake / Sydney / Permanent / $160,000 + super

About the company

A growing technology consultancy based in Sydney, focused on Data, Cloud, and AI solutions. This business supports clients with scalable, innovative technologies and offers a collaborative, fast-paced environment with space for growth and experimentation.

They are happy to accommodate a Jan or Feb start based on notice periods, but would start interviews this side of Christmas.

About the role

This Senior Data Engineer role sits within a small, high-performing team. You‚Äôll take the lead on delivering Snowflake-centric data engineering solutions‚Äîfrom solution design and architecture through to implementation and optimisation. You‚Äôll mentor junior engineers, guide best practices, and work across modern cloud platforms that heavily leverage Snowflake as the core data environment.

Benefits
$160,000 + Super
Work with cutting-edge Snowflake, cloud, and AI technologies
Supportive and innovative team culture
Flexible working arrangements
Opportunities to grow and take ownership of solutions
Duties/Key responsibilities
Design, build, and optimise robust Snowflake data pipelines, models, and warehouse solutions
Lead client delivery engagements and manage key stakeholder relationships
Mentor junior team members and champion Snowflake and cloud engineering best practices
Work across cloud-based platforms including AWS / GCP and Snowflake, with exposure to Databricks where relevant
Skills and experience
Strong experience in Snowflake architecture, data modelling, ETL/ELT processes, and scalable data pipelines
Proficient in Python, SQL, and/or Spark
Hands-on experience with Snowflake and complementary cloud environments such as Google Cloud or Databricks
Comfortable working directly with clients in consultative, solution-focused engagements
Knowledge of visualisation tools (e.g., Tableau, Power BI) and DevOps practices
Bonus: experience with Snowpipe, streaming data, big data frameworks, or data governance and security best practices
